        <span class=3D"a-size-base cr-lightbox-review-body">
            The Matrix is a film classic, and it will continue to appreciat=
e as we ascend into the technological advancements of today's world. It's i=
ncredibly odd watching this movie 20 years later now, and seeing how some o=
f the assumptions about the internet, technology, and society were addresse=
d here. All of that withheld, it's still a great piece of sci-fi action tha=
t has rarely been met with a competitor or similar style. A lot of the styl=
